        "body": "## Summary\n- Treat target AGENTS.md as optional repository-authored review policy and guidance in item and commit review prompts.\n- Keep AGENTS.md below ClawSweeper/system/developer instructions and preserve existing repository profile and owner fallback behavior.\n- Add focused prompt tests for the policy-overlay semantics and bump REVIEW_POLICY_VERSION so existing complete reviews refresh.\n\n## Source\n- Implements https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/issues/185.\n- Builds on the narrower read-and-follow AGENTS.md work from https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/pull/173; credit to @Takhoffman for both the source issue and groundwork.\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- In prompts/review-item.md, concrete actionable AGENTS.md conflicts in PR diffs can become reviewFindings using existing finding kinds; issue or non-patch policy conflicts should route through existing risks, bestSolution, solutionAssessment, or workReason fields.\n- In prompts/review-commit.md, AGENTS.md conflicts should become findings only when they create concrete bug, regression, security, compatibility, validation, supply-chain, or similar maintainer-relevant risk.\n- Do not add a parser, new target-repo config, schema fields, labels, dispatcher/webhook changes, or repository-profile migration.\n- Add the required CHANGELOG.md entry if it is not already present.\n\n## Validation\n- pnpm run test:unit\n- pnpm run check\n\nClawSweeper 🐠 replacement reef notes:\n- Cluster: issue-openclaw-clawsweeper-185\n- Source PRs: none\n- Credit: Source issue by @Takhoffman: https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/issues/185.; Preserve context from the already-merged groundwork PR by @Takhoffman: https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/pull/173.\n- Validation: pnpm run test:unit; pnpm run check\n- Replacement reason: ClawSweeper could not update the source PR branch directly, so it opened a writable replacement PR instead.\n\nfish notes: model gpt-5.5, reasoning high; reviewed against f2c9f9